<subSubSection id="E6B41BA9A07CFFF0D7D6FBC56F30F61F" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="513" pageId="0" pageNumber="511" type="description">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF2D7D6FBC5686DFA97" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Description. Labium ochreous yellow, genae lemon yellow, labrum metallic green, anteclypeus pale ochreous yellow with two darkly marked incisions on anterior edge, post-clypeus, frons and vertex metallic green, occiput black laterally, yellow medially.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF2D7D6FA9D6957F899" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">
Pronotum velvety black with green metallic sheen and with lemon-yellow dorso-lateral longitudinal bands. The posterior edge of the pronotum is drawn out into a broad almost rectangular lobe with distinct angles and subparallel sides (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07CFFF2D794FA1E6B33FA4F" box="[238,368,1444,1479]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[274,328,2375,2405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 2. C. draconica n.sp., a, prothorax, dorsal view; b, synthorax, lateral view; c, 1St, 2nd, 3rd, and beginning of 4th abdominal segments, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244195/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). Thoracic dorsum very bright metallic green with bright lemonyellow humeral stripes; the latter cross the humeral suture leaving a strip of metallic green above the suture anteriorly and passing completely on to the mesepimeron at posterior end (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07CFFF2D5D5F99B6976F9CB" box="[687,821,1569,1604]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[274,328,2375,2405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 2. C. draconica n.sp., a, prothorax, dorsal view; b, synthorax, lateral view; c, 1St, 2nd, 3rd, and beginning of 4th abdominal segments, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244195/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
). Most of the mesepimeron metallic green. Part of the metepistemum also metallic green, but anterior end including the area of the metastigma, a strip at the lower edge, and cuneiform spot at postero-dorsal angle yellow. Metepimeron light yellowish with black upper edge, covered by heavy whitish pruinosity in mature specimens. Legs black on lateral surfaces and brown on mesial surfaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF2D7D1F8AD6B6BF7BB" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Wings hyaline with a light yellow tinge, especially distinct on petioles and at anterior edges. Pterostigma elongate, 2.8-3.1 mm., covering 3t-5 cells, distinctly bicolorous, black proximally and yellow to reddish brown (depending on degree of maturity) distally. No banding on wings of available specimens. R4+5 at subnodus (see Fig. I). The cell between Rl and R2+5 is often crossed, but there is much variation in this respect, even between right and left wings of the same specimen.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF2D7D0F7836928F6D3" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">
Abdomen dorsally metallic green with yellow mid-dorsal line on segments 2-5 (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07CFFF2D7ADF7D96B10F70F" box="[215,339,2144,2183]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[274,328,2375,2405]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 2. C. draconica n.sp., a, prothorax, dorsal view; b, synthorax, lateral view; c, 1St, 2nd, 3rd, and beginning of 4th abdominal segments, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244195/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). An indistinct transverse crescentic black spot near posterior edge of each segment, distal to which the median line becomes abruptly narrower. Heavy bluish pruinosity on proximal part of tergite 1 and on tegites 9 and 10. Abdomen ventrally light brown with black mid-ventral line. Posterior edge of 10th tergite cut out medially and projecting backwards dorso-laterally (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07CFFF2D249F6B76FECF6A7" box="[1331,1455,2315,2352]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,243,985,1015]" captionTargetBox="[571,1052,490,965]" captionText="Fig. 4. C. draconica n.sp., terminal part of penis in lateral (a) and ventral (b) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246286/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
); the projections marked with reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF0D7D0F6DB69E1FEBD" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="513" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">The ♀ is very similar to the ♂ in coloration, but there is no pruinosity on the 9th and 10th tergites of the abdomen. The shape of the pronotum is the same in both sexes. The posterior edge of the loth tergite is evenly convex in the ~, not SInUOus. Cerci slender, brown with black tips.</paragraph>
<footnote id="CDB5542CA07CFFF2D237F67D6FC6F669" box="[1357,1413,2503,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07CFFF2D237F67D6FC6F669" blockId="0.[128,1484,1086,2529]" box="[1357,1413,2503,2529]" pageId="0" pageNumber="511">33-2</paragraph>
</footnote>
<caption id="FAD118AAA07DFFF3D6D0FB776F2FFB63" box="[426,1388,1224,1259]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244193/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" targetBox="[541,1326,255,1204]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07DFFF3D6D0FB776F2FFB63" blockId="1.[426,1388,255,1259]" box="[426,1388,1224,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="512">
Fig. 1. 
<taxonomicName id="69AE33A1A07DFFF3D558FB776896FB62" authority="Balinsky, 1956" authorityName="Balinsky" authorityYear="1956" box="[546,725,1227,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Chlorolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicus">C. draconica</taxonomicName>
n.sp., holotype ♂ (magnified by about 1'4).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FAD118AAA07DFFF3D668F6FD6E9DF60F" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244195/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" targetBox="[274,972,1351,2356]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07DFFF3D668F6FD6E9DF60F" blockId="1.[273,1615,2373,2481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="512">
Fig. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="69AE33A1A07DFFF3D6FAF6FD6871F6EC" authority="Balinsky, 1956" authorityName="Balinsky" authorityYear="1956" box="[384,562,2373,2405]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Chlorolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicus">C. draconica</taxonomicName>
n.sp., a, prothorax, dorsal view; b, synthorax, lateral view; c, 1St, 2nd, 3rd, and beginning of 4th abdominal segments, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FAD118AAA07DFFF3D66BF6296E51F638" box="[273,1042,2447,2481]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244197/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" targetBox="[1176,1594,1562,2358]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07DFFF3D66BF6296E51F638" blockId="1.[273,1615,2373,2481]" box="[273,1042,2447,2481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="512">
Fig. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="69AE33A1A07DFFF3D6F0F629687DF638" authority="Balinsky, 1956" authorityName="Balinsky" authorityYear="1956" box="[394,574,2449,2481]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Chlorolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicus">C. draconica</taxonomicName>
n.sp., accessory genitalia of ♂.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07EFFF0D7C3FE806F93FE39" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">
Genitalia, ♂'. Posterior hamules with distinct subterminal notch on inner edge (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07EFFF0D7E4FEDF6B4BFE00" box="[158,264,357,392]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[273,327,2451,2481]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 3. C. draconica n.sp., accessory genitalia of ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244197/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Penis (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07EFFF0D6CAFEDF6859FE00" box="[432,538,357,392]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[189,243,985,1015]" captionTargetBox="[571,1052,490,965]" captionText="Fig. 4. C. draconica n.sp., terminal part of penis in lateral (a) and ventral (b) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246286/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) with short and broad fossa subterminally, and with a terminal hook, partially covered by the membraneous flap at the tip of the penis.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FAD118AAA07EFFF0D7C7FC636FEBFC7F" box="[189,1448,985,1015]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246286/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513" targetBox="[571,1052,490,965]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07EFFF0D7C7FC636FEBFC7F" blockId="2.[189,1448,985,1015]" box="[189,1448,985,1015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">
Fig. 4. 
<taxonomicName id="69AE33A1A07EFFF0D64DFC636BAFFC7F" authority="Balinsky, 1956" authorityName="Balinsky" authorityYear="1956" box="[311,492,985,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Chlorolestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="513" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconicus">C. draconica</taxonomicName>
n.sp., terminal part of penis in lateral (a) and ventral (b) view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="FAD118AAA07EFFF0D7B6F9556E57F8A5" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244199/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513" targetBox="[336,1285,1080,1752]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="AE114822A07EFFF0D7B6F9556E57F8A5" blockId="2.[204,1439,1080,1837]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5. C. draconica n.sp., loth abdominal segment of ♂ with anal appendages in lateral (a) and dorsal (b) view.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07EFFF0D7EFF8D46B5AF7B4" blockId="2.[146,1495,1898,2294]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">
Superior anal appendages without teeth or lobes on inner margin, evenly curved in the horizontal plane, the tips only slightly bent downwards (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07EFFF0D3C7F82D6F67F832" box="[1213,1316,1943,1978]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[204,258,1775,1805]" captionTargetBox="[336,1285,1080,1752]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 5. C. draconica n.sp., loth abdominal segment of ♂ with anal appendages in lateral (a) and dorsal (b) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244199/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Inferior anal appendages bifid, outer lobe flat, broadened posteriorly and rounded at the tip, inner lobe reduced to a strong spine pointing inwards and slightly dorsad (
<figureCitation id="369554A7A07EFFF0D7E5F7AD6B46F7B4" box="[159,261,2070,2108]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[204,258,1775,1805]" captionTargetBox="[336,1285,1080,1752]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 5. C. draconica n.sp., loth abdominal segment of ♂ with anal appendages in lateral (a) and dorsal (b) view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244199/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE114822A07EFFF0D798F7E96F30F61F" blockId="2.[146,1495,1898,2294]" lastBlockId="2.[149,1497,2331,2457]" pageId="2" pageNumber="513">Abdomen ♂' 42-45 mm. ♀ 42-42.5mm. Hindwing length ♂' 6-6.5 mm. ♀ 34mm. Hindwing breadth ♂' mm. ♀ 6.5mm. Ratio abdomenfhindwing ♂' 1.32-1.41 ♀ 1.23-1.25 Localities, Found along streams on the eastern slopes of the Drakensberg in the Mont Aux Sources area, only at higher altitudes, as on Gudu River, just below the Gudu Falls, and on the Tugela River above the Tugela Gorge.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
